    "actions_taken": [
      "BSEE notified by phone and email at 1611 hours on 27 April 2025",
      "Incident report submitted to BSEE eWell Incident Reporting System on 06 May 2025",
      "Seven bottles recovered from top deck and shipped to shore",
      "Cantium required all nitrogen cylinders on their platforms across the Gulf to be inspected"
    ],
    "summary": "On 27 April 2025 at 1520 hours, a nitrogen bottle rack containing 12 bottles (300 cubic feet each) exploded on the top deck of Main Pass 42 Delta platform. One corroded nitrogen bottle ruptured, causing a chain reaction that compromised the aluminum rack and sent bottles flying across the platform. Four bottles went overboard into the Gulf, seven were scattered on deck, and one remained in the damaged rack. No personnel were injured despite being in the vicinity. The bottles were daisy-chained together with 1/4 inch stainless steel tubing, which caused the cascade failure. Investigation revealed the bottles were at least 1 year overdue for inspection.",
